section.heading: Unlawful disclosure of federal tax information; penalty.

content.p: It is unlawful for any person to divulge or make known federal tax information obtained pursuant to 26 U.S.C. s. 6103, except in accordance with a proper judicial order or as otherwise provided by law for use in the administration of the tax laws of this state, and such information is confidential and exempt from the provisions of s.119.07(1).

It is unlawful for any person to divulge or make known federal tax information obtained pursuant to 26 U.S.C. s. 6103, except in accordance with a proper judicial order or as otherwise provided by law for use in the administration of the tax laws of this state, and such information is confidential and exempt from the provisions of s.119.07(1).
Any person who violates the provisions of this section is guilty of a misdemeanor of the first degree, punishable as provided in s.775.082or s.775.083.
